cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the existence and complexity of finding conveyor belts for sets of disjoint disks in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The problem involves discrete mathematics, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as well. Finally, the paper involves some graph theory, which could make cs.GT (Graph Theory) a possible sub-category.
